error handling

204 - no content ie. delete request res.sendStatus(204)
400 - bad format, wrong keys/values, client done something wrong
404 - reasonable request but doesnt exist
422 - eg. trying to post something wtih unique key thats already in the db
500 - cant figure out the error-last resort


X get /asdsa :404
X get topics?query :200/500
X sort_by col doesnt exist :400/200 [articles, comments] -> send({msg: err.error})
-order !== asc/desc :400/200 [articles, articles/id/comments, topics]
X author/topic doesnt exist :404 [~, ~, ~]
X author/topic exists but nothing associated with it :200 and empty array [~,~]
X bad id eg str instead of num :400 [~, ~, ~]

X no inc_votes on body :200 give unchanged back [~, ~]
X invalid inc_votes :400 [comments/comment_id, articles/article_id]
X something else on body :200/400 [comments/comment_id, articles/article_id]



promise.all for eg.house that doesnt exist 

sednwizards
promise.all([gethouses(), get wizards()]).then(([house, wizards]) => {

})

custom err handling::
next({status: 400, msg: 'bad request'})


app.all('/*', (req, res, next) => {
    next({status: 400, msg: 'bad request'})
})

app.use((err, req, res, next) => {
    if (err.status) {
    res.status(err.status).send({msg: err.msg})
}
}) 


.onDelete('CASCADE')
